The General Rule
<tagName> Some Content </tagName>

______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

Format :
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
    <head>
    <!--Meta Data-->
    <title></title>
    </head>

    <body>
        <!--Content goes here-->
    </body>
</html>
______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

General Tags <tag>~~~~~</tag> :     {All except mentioned are block level elements}
p                                               -                    paragraph
title                                           -                    Title of the web Page
html                                            -                    Root Tag
head                                            -                    All functionalities that don't appear in body tag
body                                            -                    Contents that appear in web page
h1 - h6                                         -                    Heading tags of the page
strong or b [Inline]                            -                    Bold  
em or i [Inline]                                -                    Italisize
ol                                              -                    Ordered List
ul                                              -                    Unordered List
li                                              -                    List Entry tag
tr                                              -                    Table Row
td                                              -                    Table Data
thead                                           -                    Heading Block
tbody                                           -                    Body Block
th                                              -                    Table Header
_______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

Attributes :  <tag name1 = "value1" name2 = "value2"></tag>
->  Adds additional Information to html elements.
->  takes a key(property), value(corresponding value) pair.

image                                           -                   <img src = "dog"> {closing is optional} and only to write.
anchor                                          -                   <a href = "www.google.com">HyperLink</a>
table                                           -                   <table border="">******</table>
_______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

Forms in HTML : Useful for taking input in HTML (Interactive Control)

form  tag : Shell or Container for all different type of inputs
  * represents a document section containing interactive controls for submitting information.
  * It Sends Data from the form to a server.
  
  
  <form action="where to sent the data" method="post"> 
    !-- All of the inputs will go here -->
  </form>
  
  method = "get"  -> Retrieving Data
  method = "post" -> Posting the data to server
                             *******_________********
input  tag : Block where different inputs will be given by the user. 

  <input type="type"> [type = {text, password, email, date, color, file, checkbox};]
  Placeholder is an attribute used to fill the default input.
                             *******_________
 -> checked attribute in checkbox checks even after the page is loaded.                     
                             
Label tag : It represents Caption for an item in userinterface.

Syntax1 : <label> username: <input type="password" placeholder="username"></input>
Syntax2 : <label for="username">Username:</label>
          <input id="username" type="password" placeholder="username"></input>
-> In input tag for radio button name tag if there are multiple attributes and assign value tag to name tag for correct data transfer.
-> for select tag we no need to mention value (for simple texts) because the value of input will be taken automatically by browser,
    but for any other charecters it should be sent in select tag.
 textarea tag : for input with many words(lines).

Validations: Checking for valid inputs. 
    Ex : required attribute inside a input tag
_______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
Div{Block level}, span{Inline} : Generic Container used for Grouping
